::: {.column width="50%"}
-   Mean squares (MS):
    -   average variation for each source
-   If groups differ → $MS_{groups}$ is large relative to $MS_{error}$
-   Larger $F$ → stronger evidence of differences among groups
-   P-value: probability of observing this $F$ if all group means are equal
